        <em
          >This essay discusses historical file-sharing communities as social and
          economic systems. It is not an endorsement of copyright infringement;
          the mechanics we celebrate — reciprocity, quality standards,
          self-governance — are content-neutral, and xNet is built for scenes
          that own or have the right to share what they keep.</em
